To date, several studies have examined the association between ambient air pollution and the incidence or mortality of COVID-19 around world, through time-series, regression or correlation test (
 Table 3 ). Although the studies has some notable differences as compared to our work, sepecially in the statistic model, the results from different countries and regions, including China (
 Xu et al., 2020a; 
 Zhu et al., 2020), the USA (
 Bashir et al., 2020; 
 Hendryx and Luo, 2020) and Italy (
 Fattorini and Regoli, 2020; 
 Ogen, 2020; 
 Zoran et al., 2020a, 
 b), are similar to ours and generally point to positive association between air pollution and risk of COVID-19.
